In this article, President Donald Trump issues a proclamation declaring March 2018 as Women's History Month. He acknowledges the significant contributions that women have made throughout American history, highlighting examples such as Mary Katherine Goddard, Olive Ann Beech, and Marva Collins. Trump emphasizes the importance of supporting women's economic empowerment and promoting family-friendly policies. He mentions initiatives to increase lending to women-owned businesses and to mentor and educate the next generation of women leaders. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe Women's History Month and celebrate International Women's Day on March 8, 2018.